# Phone Mockup + Expanded Input Types

## What Changed

### 7 Specific Input Types
Replaced the single "Text Input" with 7 pre-configured input variants:

| Input | Icon | Pre-set Defaults |
|---|---|---|
| Text Input | ✏️ | label: "Full Name", keyboard: default |
| Email Input | 📧 | label: "Email", keyboard: email-address |
| Password Input | 🔒 | secureTextEntry + show/hide toggle |
| Phone Input | 📞 | keyboard: phone-pad |
| Number Input | 🔢 | keyboard: numeric |
| Search Input | 🔍 | clearable: true |
| Multiline Input | 📄 | multiline: true |

All share the same [CustomInput](file:///Users/tripookieuser/Documents/untitled%20folder/nativecn-ui/registry/components/custom-input/CustomInput.tsx#20-98) component — they differ only in default prop values.

### Phone Device Mockup
The plain canvas was replaced with a realistic phone frame:
- **iOS mode** — Dynamic Island notch, status bar icons, home indicator bar
- **Android mode** — Standard status bar, navigation buttons (square, circle, triangle)
- **Toggle** above the device to switch between platforms

### Visual Component Previews
Inside the device, components now render as styled visual approximations:
- Inputs → labeled bordered fields with placeholder text
- Buttons → gradient pill
- Headings → large bold text
- DatePicker → date selector row
- Switch → label + toggle

